# Project Structure

This project uses a Memory Bank architecture for maintaining project context across sessions.

## Key Directories and Files

- [memory-bank/](mdc:memory-bank/) - Contains all project documentation and context
  - [projectbrief.md](mdc:memory-bank/projectbrief.md) - Foundation document defining core requirements
  - [productContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/productContext.md) - Product purpose and user experience goals
  - [systemPatterns.md](mdc:memory-bank/systemPatterns.md) - System architecture and design patterns
  - [techContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/techContext.md) - Technical details and constraints
  - [activeContext.md](mdc:memory-bank/activeContext.md) - Current work focus and next steps
  - [progress.md](mdc:memory-bank/progress.md) - Project status and achievements
- [.cursorrules](mdc:.cursorrules) - Project intelligence and conventions
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - Main entry point for the application

## Navigation Guidelines

1. Always start by reading the Memory Bank files to understand the current project state
